Here are the exact mathematical specifications for the 3 Layout Variants:
(Note: The 13x19 page always has a 0.5-inch left margin and the grid always occupies a 12x18 inch bounding box, leaving a 1-inch margin at the bottom for the label).
Variant 1: "4x3 Polaroid (18 per sheet)"
Grid: 3 columns x 6 rows (Max 18 images).
Outer Cell: 4 inches Wide x 3 inches High.
Image Processing: Crop to a 2.5 (W) : 3 (H) aspect ratio. Rotate 90 degrees clockwise.
Inner Placement: Final image drawn at 3 inches W x 2.5 inches H.
Offsets inside cell: X offset = +0.75 inches (from left of cell), Y offset = +0.25 inches (from bottom of cell).
Variant 2: "3x2 Polaroid (36 per sheet)"
Grid: 4 columns x 9 rows (Max 36 images).
Outer Cell: 3 inches Wide x 2 inches High.
Image Processing: Crop to a 1.7 (W) : 2.25 (H) aspect ratio. Rotate 90 degrees clockwise.
Inner Placement: Final image drawn at 2.25 inches W x 1.7 inches H.
Offsets inside cell: X offset = +0.57 inches (from left of cell), Y offset = +0.15 inches (from bottom of cell).
Variant 3: "3x3 Square (24 per sheet)"
Grid: 4 columns x 6 rows (Max 24 images).
Outer Cell: 3 inches Wide x 3 inches High.
Image Processing: Crop to a 1:1 aspect ratio (Square). DO NOT rotate this variant.
Inner Placement: Final image drawn at 2.6 inches W x 2.6 inches H.
Offsets inside cell: X offset = +0.2 inches (from left of cell), Y offset = +0.2 inches (from bottom of cell).
